        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: add native MiniMax provider support (+ reasoning-tag stripping)",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAdds **MiniMax** as a first-class, natively-supported LLM provider, plus a small, opt-in **reasoning-tag stripper** to keep MiniMax (and, later, any chosen provider) output clean.\n\n### 1. Native MiniMax support\nMiniMax exposes an OpenAI-compatible chat-completions API, so this mirrors the existing `nvidia`/`zai` gateway pattern rather than introducing a bespoke client.\n\n- New model ids: `minimax/<model>` (e.g. `minimax/MiniMax-M3`, `minimax/MiniMax-M2.5-highspeed`).\n- Auth via `MINIMAX_API_KEY`; optional endpoint override via `MINIMAX_BASE_URL` or `minimax.baseUrl` in `~/.summarize/config.json` (default `https://api.minimax.io/v1`).\n- Wired end-to-end: `model-spec`, provider profiles/capabilities, `generate-text` (+streaming), run env/engine/plan/contexts/flows, config (types/env/sections/apiKeys), daemon (models, agent-model, chat, flow-context, env-snapshot), costs, CLI help, and docs (`README.md`, `docs/llm.md`, `docs/commands/summarize.md`).\n- Like all native providers, MiniMax is only used when explicitly requested (`--model minimax/...`); it is **not** added to the built-in `auto` candidate list, so default selection behavior is unchanged.\n\n### 2. Reasoning-tag stripping\nMiniMax's M-series are reasoning models that inline their chain-of-thought as `<think>…</think>` in the chat-completions **text** channel (first-party providers keep reasoning on a separate channel and never leak). New `src/llm/reasoning-tags.ts`:\n\n- `stripReasoningTags()` — removes a leading `<think>…</think>` block (and a dangling `</think>`) from a complete response; conservative (won't touch mid-content tags or text that merely mentions \"think\").\n- `createReasoningTagFilter()` — stateful streaming variant that suppresses the block across delta boundaries, then forwards the answer.\n- **Single source of truth for scope:** `REASONING_TAG_STRIP_PROVIDERS` (a `Set`). Changing which providers get stripping is a one-line edit.\n\n### Design notes\n- The strip set defaults to **`minimax` only**. This intentionally does **not** change behavior for existing providers (`nvidia`, `zai`, `ollama`, etc.) even though they could exhibit the same leak with reasoning models — flip them on later by adding to the set if desired.\n- No defaults, output formats, or auto-selection rules were changed.\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [x] `pnpm typecheck` — clean\n- [x] `pnpm lint` (oxlint, type-aware) — clean\n- [x] `pnpm format` (oxfmt) — clean\n- [x] `pnpm exec vitest run` — full suite **2171 passed / 41 skipped**, no regressions\n- [x] New unit tests: `tests/llm.reasoning-tags.test.ts` (leading block, dangling close, passthrough, mid-content safety, streaming split across deltas, no-close flush) + added `minimax` cases to `tests/model-spec.test.ts` and `tests/llm.provider-capabilities.test.ts`\n- [x] Live end-to-end against the real MiniMax API (`MINIMAX_API_KEY`):\n  - `minimax/MiniMax-M3`, `minimax/MiniMax-M2.5-highspeed`, `minimax/MiniMax-M2`\n  - Verified correct provider attribution, token usage, and cost reporting\n  - Verified `<think>` reasoning is stripped in **both** streaming and non-streaming (`--json`) paths, while the final summary is preserved\n\nMade with [Cursor](https://cursor.com)",
